<h2 id="section-top">Occupational therapy services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=29674">Derbyshire Community Health Services NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent59e6197bdb104095a58a9fd5dfa605db">
</div>
<p><strong>Occupational therapy - helping people to achieve as much as they can for themselves and get the most out of life.'</strong></p>
<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p>Occupational therapy services identify the problem areas that patients may have in their everyday lives and helps them to work out practical solutions to regain or improve their independence and wellbeing within the home, work and social life.</p>
<p>Our services include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Assessments of daily living </li>
<li>Diagnosis of therapy/      treatments </li>
<li>Rehabilitation programmes      (eg. upper limb rehabilitation, splinting, vocational/ workplace      rehabilitation) </li>
<li>Advice and education (eg.      lifestyle management approaches including; pacing, task analysis, activity      modification, joint protection, energy conservation, relaxation, equipment      assessment/ provision, self management skills). </li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p>All our patients are assessed and treated on an individual, one to one basis and may also be referred to an appropriate group therapy programme.</p>
<p>Out-patient Occupational Therapy Services are available for adults of any age with musculoskeletal (ie. injury, damage or disorder of the joints or other tissues eg. bones, ligaments, tendons, muscles, nerves), rheumatological and orthapaedic conditions.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Accessing the service</strong></p>
<p>Referrals are accepted from GPs, Consultants and Health Care Professionals. Self referrals are also accepted if the patient has been known to the service within the previous six months.<br/><br/>The referral should be made in writing, and for urgent referrals, by fax to the relevant service location.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Locations</strong></p>
<p>Occupational Therapy Services are provided at Ilkeston and Ripley  Community Hospitals, with satellite clinics at Heanor Memorial Hospital  and St.Oswald’s Hospital.</p>
<p>Contact each site for service opening times.</p>
<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p><strong>Contact</strong></p>
<p>For further information contact Janice Bryan, locality manager for Amber Valley/ Erewash and South Derbyshire Dales;</p>
<p>Tel: 01773 571442</p>
<p><a href="mailto:janice.bryan@dchs.nhs.uk">janice.bryan@dchs.nhs.uk</a></p>
<p> </p>
